<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-701] ClusterDumper writes to System.out or local filesystem only (I would like to write to s3 when running on Elastic MapReduce)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-701</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;At the end of a kmeans job at EMR, I like to look through the clusters.  Unfortunately ClusterDumper writes to System.out or a local file.  I added a small conditional to examine the filename to see if it starts with s3n://, and if so to open up a FileSystem to write to s3 instead of to the local filesystem so that the output file is available after the cluster is shut down.  I am creating the patch now (tests are still running from the change in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-700&quot; title=&quot;When running &amp;#39;seqdirectory&amp;#39; on Amazon Elastic MapReduce, FileSystem.get() fails due to use of FileSystem.get(conf) instead of FileSystem.get(uri, conf)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-700&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-700&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), so I will add the patch to this issue shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Amazon Elastic MapReduce&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
